      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2018-04-10T19:32:13Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <actionDate>2017-06-28</actionDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>This bill requires the Departments of Defense (DOD) and of Homeland Security (DHS) to conduct a joint study on aliens who are or were veterans who were removed from the United States between January 1990 and January 2017. </p> <p>DOD and DHS shall then report to Congress on: </p> <ul> <li> the number of aliens removed by Immigration and Customs Enforcement during such period who served on active duty or in a reserve component of the U.S. Armed Forces for more than 180 days,</li> <li>the country of origin for each such alien,</li> <li> the number of such aliens who were discharged or released from service under honorable conditions,</li> <li>the grounds for removal under the Immigration and Nationality Act for each such alien,</li> <li>whether each such alien appealed the removal order,</li> <li>the length of time each such alien served in the Armed Forces,</li> <li>the number of such aliens who were deployed overseas as members of the Armed Forces,</li> <li>the number who served on active duty in a combat theater of operations, and</li> <li>the number who were awarded service medals.</li> </ul>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2017-06-28T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
